<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="269" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1030,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1210,1236]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small brown 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1895" box="[482,627,1211,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Platyphyllini">Platyphyllini</taxonomicName>
with tegmina barely covering abdomen and hairy legs (
<figureCitation box="[1253,1330,1211,1237]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,413,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[163,1424,396,1956]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male holotype in dorsal view, B. same in lateral view, C. female paratype to same scale as B (specimen cbt019s01)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677989/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1344,1382,1211,1237]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,248,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,185,893]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,181,900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male habitus, B. male subgenital plate in ventral view, C. male left cercus in dorsal view, D. male pronotum in dorsal view, E. ovipositor of female (pencil drawings done in October 2003, after holotype and a paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677993/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">2A</figureCitation>
). All genicular lobes armed. Male with pronotum posteriorly widened and disc with three white callose spots: one in the middle of anterior margin and two close together at rear margin (
<figureCitation box="[890,991,1283,1309]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,413,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[163,1424,396,1956]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male holotype in dorsal view, B. same in lateral view, C. female paratype to same scale as B (specimen cbt019s01)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677989/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1004,1040,1283,1309]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,248,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,185,893]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,181,900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male habitus, B. male subgenital plate in ventral view, C. male left cercus in dorsal view, D. male pronotum in dorsal view, E. ovipositor of female (pencil drawings done in October 2003, after holotype and a paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677993/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">2D</figureCitation>
), base of left tegmen opaque, right tegmen with transparent mirror. Female without white spots and considerably larger than male (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1310,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,413,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[163,1424,396,1956]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male holotype in dorsal view, B. same in lateral view, C. female paratype to same scale as B (specimen cbt019s01)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677989/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1030,2029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,541,1354,1381]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Additional descriptive notes:</emphasis>
Fastigium short, scapi of antennae with prominent spine. Prosternum with fairly long spines. Male with a small whitish spot on tips of fore and middle femora and several indistinct spots on hind femora. Middle femora with 3 ventral spines in apical portion, hind femora with 4 small spines (
<quantity box="[1219,1262,1426,1453]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
a female specimen with only one hind femur). Spines of inner genicular lobe of forefemur slightly larger than outer ones, contrariwise on hind femur. Male subgenital plate elongate, terminally emarginate, with long styli (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1301,1499,1525]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,248,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,185,893]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,181,900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male habitus, B. male subgenital plate in ventral view, C. male left cercus in dorsal view, D. male pronotum in dorsal view, E. ovipositor of female (pencil drawings done in October 2003, after holotype and a paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677993/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), male cerci with small sclerotized internal spinule (
<figureCitation box="[604,695,1535,1561]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,248,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,185,893]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,181,900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male habitus, B. male subgenital plate in ventral view, C. male left cercus in dorsal view, D. male pronotum in dorsal view, E. ovipositor of female (pencil drawings done in October 2003, after holotype and a paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677993/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor robust and slightly upcurved (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1288,1535,1561]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1412,413,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-51@1.[163,1424,396,1956]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male holotype in dorsal view, B. same in lateral view, C. female paratype to same scale as B (specimen cbt019s01)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677989/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1303,1337,1535,1561]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,248,924,948]" captionTargetBox="[154,1430,185,893]" captionTargetId="figure-27@2.[151,1436,181,900]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mikrischyrum musicum: A. male habitus, B. male subgenital plate in ventral view, C. male left cercus in dorsal view, D. male pronotum in dorsal view, E. ovipositor of female (pencil drawings done in October 2003, after holotype and a paratype)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5677993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5677993/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">2E</figureCitation>
), female subgenital plate triangular with delicate terminal notch.
</paragraph>
